해외여행지 추천, 영화 스타워즈 장소 신비로워
​
​
​
2018년 새해 첫 포스팅은 2018년에 가장 하고싶고 가보고싶은 해외여행지 추천으로 시작해볼까 한다.
여행을 떠나고 싶은데, 이런이유 저런이유들로 그동안 못가본 곳들이 너무 많지만,
이렇게라도 포스팅으로 글을 남기며,,, 언젠가 꼭 가보리라는 희망만으로도 기쁨이 있다.
​
영화를 볼때마다 그곳이 어디든 가보고싶은 곳이 너무 많았는데, 특히 SF영화를 볼땐,
저런곳이 실제 존재할까...? 라는 궁금증이 참 컸더랬다.
​
그중 한 영화는 영화 스타워즈.
알고보니, 스타워즈 영화의 실제 촬영지가 있었다고 한다.
사진들로 보는내내 신비로움이 가득해 직접 눈으로 보고싶다는 바램이 가득해서
해외여행지 추천하며, 공유해본다.
​
​
​
​
​
​
Luke Skywalker's igloo (Chott El Jerid, Nefta, Tunisia):
The igloo exterior of Luke's house was filmed about 300 kilometers away on the dried-up salt lake of Chott El Jerid. It was rebuilt for "Attack of the Clones," and later restored by a fan.
​
​
​루크 스카이워커의 이글루
​
​
​
​
​
Scarif (Laamu Atoll, Maldives):
In "Rogue One," the Laamu Atoll, a string of islands that form part of the Maldives archipelago, plays Scarif, an Imperial planet where Death Star plans are stored.
몰디브, 내가 가본곳이구나...ㅎㅎ 신혼여행 해외여행지 추천에 빠질수 없는 곳이지.
​
​
​
​
​
​
Salar De Uyuni in Bolivia:
In "The Last Jedi," the stunning salt flats of Salar De Uyuni in Bolivia stand in for the planet of Crait, scene of a battle between Resistance and the First Order.
​
​
​우유니, 볼리비아 포토시주에 있는 도시. 너무 가보고 싶다.. 영화 스타워즈 'The Last Jedi'에서..
​
​
​
​
​
Luke Skywalker's home (Hotel Sidi Driss, Matmata, Tunisia):
Built centuries ago by indigenous Berbers, this subterranean cave homes were converted to a hotel which George Lucas used as Luke Skywalker's childhood home in the original "Star Wars" film. It's still a hotel and contains props used in "Attack of the Clones."​
​
​
​
​튀니지의 호텔, 시디드리스.. 이게 호텔이었다니...
시디드리스 호텔은 영화 스타워즈 시리즈 촬영지로, 세계 50대 이색 호텔이라고도 한다.
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
Imperial base, Scarif (Canary Wharf Station, London):
The futuristic steel, glass and concrete of London's Canary Wharf metro station doubles as an Imperial base on Scarif. The station is regularly used by bankers, so arguably has experience of the dark side of The Force.
​
​
카나리 워프 스테이션. 런던의 지하철역.
Massassi outpost  (Tikal National Park, Guatemala):
These thousand-year-old Mayan ruins came within a whisker of being destroyed by the Death Star in "A New Hope." The film sees the temples used as a Rebel base.
​과테말라의 티칼 국립공원으로 정글 한가운데 울창한 초목들로 둘러싸인 이 곳은 마야문명의 중요한 유적지 중 하나라고 한다.
​
​
​
​
​
Endor (Redwood National and State Parks, California):
The thrilling speedbike chases in "The Return of the Jedi" through the forests of Endor -- the home of the furry Ewoks -- were filmed among California's giant redwoods.
​
캘리포니아의 레드우드 국립공원.... 아... 예전에 해외여행지 추천받아 가본곳인데...
이런 곳이 있었던가.... +_+ 다시 가봐야 겠다.
Eadu (Reynisfjara, Iceland):
The black sand beach of Reynisfjara, a wild stretch of North Atlantic coastline close to the small town of Vik and Iceland's southernmost tip, appears in "Rogue One" as the stormy planet of Eadu.
​
​아이스랜드, 레이니스파라 ..
아이슬란드 여행의 필수코스로 주상절리가 압권린 레이니스피야라 해변 ... 보고싶다..
​
​
​
​
​
​
Naboo (Whippendell Woods, near Watford, UK):
The tranquil glades of
Whippendell Woods
, just outside London, are the setting for one of the most controversial scenes in "Star Wars." It's where the widely lambasted character of Jar Jar Binks makes his debut.
​
​
​
​영화 스타워즈 말고도, 참 많이봐왔던 풍경중 한곳. 많은 SF영화에서 본듯한 느낌이 많은곳,.
​
​
​
​
​
Theed Royal Palace (Plaza de Espana, Seville, Spain):
The majestic Plaza de Espana in the Spanish city of Seville was originally built for the 1929 Ibero-American Exposition. In "Attack of the Clones" and "The Phantom Menace," it doubles as a palace on Naboo where Anakin and Padme get to stroll among its colonnades.​
​스페인,
​
Mustafar (Mount Etna, Italy):
By the magic of cinematic special effects, the lava flows on Sicilian volcano Etna provided the hellish backdrop for a battle scene between Obi-Wan and Anakin in "Revenge of the Sith."
​
​
​이탈리아의 에트나 산으로 시칠리아 섬 동쪽 해안에 위치해 있는 에트나 산은 지중해 섬에 있는 산 가운데 가장 높은 산이자
세계에서 가장 활발한성층화산이라고 한다.
​
​
​
​
Tatooine (Death Valley National Park, California/Nevada):
Although most of Tatooine was shot in Tunisia, crucial scenes in "A New Hope" were filmed in Death Valley between the Sierra Nevada mountains and Mojave Desert.
​
​
​네바다주의 죽음의 계곡. ㅎㅎㅎ 여기도 가본곳이군~
​
​
​
​
Jakku (Abu Dhabi, UAE):
For the "Force Awakens," director J.J. Abrams chose the desert of the United Arab Emirates to represent the planet Jakku.
​
​
​
​두바이... 정말 가보고싶다..
​
​
​
​
​
Jedi temple (Skellig Michael, Ireland):
The finale of "The Force Awakens" was filmed at the ruins of this seventh-century monastery, which sits on the steep sides of the island Skellig Michael. It is also appears in "The Last Jedi."
아일랜드의 스켈리그 마이클은 아이랜드 남서해안에서 떨어져있는 바위섬으로 이 바위섬 가파른 경사면에
7세기부터 자리잡고 있었던 수도원 유적이 있다. 유네스코 세계유산
​
​
​
​
​
Dubrovnik, Croatia:
The beautiful medieval city of Dubrovnik makes an appearance in "The Last Jedi" as Canto Bight, a "Star Wars" version of Las Vegas.
​
​
​
​
​
Moon of Jedha (Wadi Rum, Jordan):
In "Rogue One," the moon of Jedha is a place of spiritual significance for the Jedi. It's sandy landscape is actually Wadi Rum, a desert wilderness in southern Jordan.
​
​
​
요르단 수도 암만에서 남쪽으로 320km 지점에 위치한 사막지대로 거대한 바위산들이 장관을 이루고 있는 와디럼.
역시 유네스코 세계복합유산으로 지정.
​
​
​
Mos Espa slave quarter (Medenine, Tunisia):
When Anakin was a slave boy in "The Phantom Menace," his quarters were filmed on this real-life Tunisian street. The distinctive buildings with vaulted ceilings are ghorfas, used by Berbers to store their grain.
​
​메드닌, 튀니지
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
Lake Retreat (Villa del Balbianello, Lenno, Italy):
Managed by Italy's National Trust, the Villa del Balbianello on the shores of Lake Como, was the scene of Anakin and Padme's wedding in "Attack of the Clones." In real life, the villa is also a popular wedding destination.
​
​
​빌라 델 발비아넬로, 이태리
​
​
​
Eadu (Krafla, Iceland):
Northeastern Iceland's Krafla Volcano also doubles as the planet of Eadu in "Rogue One." It's on Eadu that Jyn Erso, played by Felicity Jones, tries to save her wounded father.
​
​
​
​
​크라플라산, 아이슬란드
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
Great Pit of Carkoon (Buttercup Valley, Yuma Desert, Arizona):
The Great Pit of Carkoon, home to the sarlacc that eats Jabba's prisoners in "Return of the Jedi," was filmed in Arizona rather than Tunisia.
​
​
​아리조나
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
​
Hoth (Hardanger Jokulen Glacier and Finse, Norway):
Exteriors of the ice world Hoth in "The Empire Strikes Back" were shot in the tiny village of Finse, Norway, and the main battlefield scenes were shot on the nearby glacier.
​
노르웨이
​
​
​
​
​
Kashyyyk (Guilin, China):
Thailand and southern China might be warm for a hairy Wookiee, but that didn't stop them being used as doubles for Chewbacca's home planet of Kashyyyk in "Revenge of the Sith."
​
​
​
​중국
